parameters: \n<\c[14]Percy\c>Darn! Still no sign of Oberon. I really hope he’s okay. I’ll search every inch of this place
if I have to, this sweltering heat won’t stop me from finding him.
Hmm, that’s weird. I didn’t expect to discover the totem just sitting here. Where is the thief?
Oh, thank goodness, you’re alright! How did you get away from your captor?
That I am, well, other than my poor singed beard! Er …
I … incapacitated him before making my escape, which involved getting a little too close
Well, I can’t do anything about your beard, but I do have the fire totem.
Oh, Splendid work, Percy! You have really come through for me.
It’s weird though, I just found it laying here. I thought the thief would have it, and
I’d have to battle them for it.
It’s a stroke of good luck! You know what they say about looking a gift horse in the mouth.
Oberon, where’d you leave the thief?
I came from there. I didn’t see you or the thief and I left no stone unturned.
Oh, fine, you’ve got me… there is no thief.
What!?!? If there’s no thief, then how did the totems get misplaced?
I didn’t try taking them if that’s what you're thinking.
Uh … I may have accidentally knocked one off the altar, it doesn’t matter how, just
I wish you would’ve just told me when I got here what really happened. I would’ve
Oh, Percy, you’re certainly one of the kindest of people I have ever met.
One thing that this whole situation has made clear is that it is time for me to find
Will you succeed me as Elysian’s new protector?
You’ve shown me you’re more than ready.
Wonderful! I know Elysian will be safe in your capable hands.
